PART II: THE WEAVER — IDENTITY, PROGRESSION, AND EXPRESSION

2.1 Anatomy & Physics — The Weaver's Body, Unwrapped

The Weaver's body is a miracle of textile engineering. It is not a solid; it is a tension network.

2.1.1 Internal Structure

The skeleton is a framework of Plied Silk Cord, a specially treated silk that is both flexible and incredibly strong. It acts like cartilage — bendable but snapping back to its original shape. The "bones" are hollow tubes of this cord, filled with a non-Newtonian fluid made of fine Lumen-Infused Cornstarch Silk that stiffens on impact. This means when the Weaver falls from a height, their legs momentarily solidify to absorb the shock, then soften. The joints are intricate Button-and-Loop mechanisms, where a polished wooden button rotates within a loop of silk braid, allowing smooth, silent movement.

2.1.2 Musculature

Muscles are bundles of Memory Wire Yarn, a nickel-titanium alloy thread wrapped in silk. They contract when a small Lumen current is passed through them. The Weaver's internal Lumen flow acts as the nervous system: tiny sparks of Threadlight travel along a network of conductive spider silk nerves to each muscle bundle, creating motion. When the Weaver sprints, the muscle bundles in the legs glow brighter from the increased Lumen flow. The Weaver does not tire in the human sense; they run on Lumen, which they replenish by collecting orbs.

2.1.3 The Skin & Mask

The outer body is wrapped in Layered Silk-Cotton Bandages, each layer dyed the Weaver's chosen palette. The wraps are not static; they subtly adjust during movement, loosening or tightening as needed. The face is covered by a Morphic Silk Mask that extends from the hairline to the neck. It's a single piece of stretch-silk, seamless. The mask is photochromic: embedded with tiny Lumen-reactive fibers that change color based on the Weaver's emotional state, which is itself linked to gameplay (taking damage = red flash; collecting a rare spool = golden wave; idle = soft pulsing blue).

The eyes are Porcelain Button Eyes with 4 holes each. They are not just cosmetic; they are the Weaver's sensory organs. The thread passing through the holes forms an X-shaped pupil. Each button is hand-painted with an iris pattern (clouds, stars, swirls, gears). The buttons can be swapped at any time from the inventory, and each pair has a minor Perception Effect: Star buttons slightly increase the range at which Lumen Orbs are visible; Gear buttons highlight moving obstacle paths a fraction of a second earlier.

2.1.4 The Cloak — A Living Garment

The Weaver's cloak is a semi-sentient entity called the Shuttle-Soul. It is woven from First Thread, a material that is a direct descendant of the First Stitch's own body thread. As such, the cloak has a rudimentary will to protect and adorn. It has 128 individual physics bones, each controlled by a blend of the Weaver's motion and its own "intention." The cloak can:

· Billow Dramatically: On command (an emote), it can flare out to three times its size for a moment, scaring minor Unravelled.
· Sense Danger: The edges of the cloak tingle (shown as a subtle visual shimmer) when an obstacle is imminent from the side, even slightly off-screen.
· Channel Power-Ups: When a power-up is active, the cloak's inner lining glows with the power-up's specific pattern and color.
· Repair Itself: Slowly, over time, when near a Heartstone, the cloak will re-stitch any frays using ambient Lumen.
· House Memories: Tiny, embroidered scenes from the player's adventures slowly appear on the cloak's underside over time, like an evolving storybook.

