PART III: SPINDLE RUN — THE INTERSTICE UNRAVELLED

3.1 The Braidway Generation — Algorithmic Weaving

The Braidway is generated by a system called the Loom Algorithm, which functions as a real-time story teller.

3.1.1 Pattern Segments Database

The developers have created a library of over 10,000 hand-crafted Pattern Segments (straightaways, turns, hills, spirals, forks). Each segment is tagged with difficulty, biome theme, obstacle density, and "mood." The algorithm selects segments dynamically to create a "run arc": a gentle start, a rising action, a peak of intensity, and a cool-down, before ramping again.

3.1.2 Dynamic Theme Integration

The Braidway's visual theme shifts based on a Realm Resonance mechanic. If your Hearth's Emberweave realm is currently undergoing a "Warp Storm" (see 4.3), the Braidway will have a 30% chance to become an "Emberweave Braidway" variant for a portion of your run. These variants change the ribbon texture, obstacle types, and collectible spools. This directly ties the state of your Hearth to your running experience.

3.1.3 Player-Responsive Pacing

The Loom Algorithm monitors your heart rate (via optional biometric controllers), your past 30 seconds of success/failure, and your current combo. If you're doing too well, it slowly increases the "entropy" — the randomness of obstacle patterns — to maintain challenge. If you've crashed twice recently, it inserts a brief "gentle strand" with easier patterns to let you recover your flow. It's a living, adaptive difficulty system.

3.1.4 Terrain Features — Full Catalog

· Loop-de-Loops: Full 360-degree rotation of the Braidway. The camera rotates with you, so "up" stays relative. Gravity shifts, so a slide becomes a wall-run for a moment. Available in 1, 2, and 3-loop variations.
· Corkscrews: The Braidway twists like a helix. You run on the inside of the spiral; lane switching is disabled, and you must jump and slide through obstacles that curve around the ribbon.
· Braidway Splits & Merges: The path splits into three parallel strands that then cross over each other. You have to jump between them to avoid obstacles. A mid-air dash between strands is rewarded.
· Memory Strands: Ephemeral, ghostly segments where the Braidway is semi-transparent and the void is filled with floating text and images from the First Stitch's memories. All movement is slowed, and the objective is to collect floating letters to form a word, unlocking a lore snippet. No obstacles, just a peaceful, narrative interlude.
· The Weaver's Chute: A 75-degree downward slope that accelerates speed to 150% of the current cap. The Braidway narrows to 2 lanes. Obstacles rush up at extreme speed. Lasts 15 seconds; surviving grants a "Chute Survivor" bonus chest.

3.2 Obstacle Ecosystem Extended — Full Bestiary

Every obstacle now has lore, behavioral patterns, and counter-play.

