PART X: SOCIAL & SHARING SYSTEMS — THE COMMUNITY LOOM

10.1 The Guest Weave — Multiplayer Intimacy

You open your Hearth to a friend via an invitation sent through the Loom Gate, which arrives as a woven scroll in their Pattern Book. When they arrive, their Weaver appears with a subtle "guest seam" aura. You set permissions via a Hospitality Tapestry: Can they build? Harvest? Take items? You can set exact areas where they can modify. All their changes are marked with a temporary, shimmering golden thread. When the guest leaves, you're presented with a Guest Alteration Log: a visual summary of everything they changed. You can "Accept" (the golden thread becomes permanent) or "Revert" (it unravels). This prevents griefing.

10.2 Community Creations — The Pattern Exchange

This is an in-game library, presented as the Grand Loom Repository, a massive, infinite spiral of spools. You can upload any blueprint, dye recipe, cloak design, embroidery patch, servitor script, or music spool. Content is tagged and rated with a 5-star system. The top-rated creations each week are featured in a "Trending Threads" showcase, and the creators are rewarded with special Cosmetic Threads. The repository is fully cross-platform.

10.3 Seasonal Thread Festivals — Live Service Integration

Every real-world season, a new Thread Festival is released. This introduces:

· A temporary Festival Realm (e.g., a realm of giant, living origami silk for a spring festival).
· A 10-part Story Quest centered on a new, temporary Spindlekin character (who becomes a permanent resident if you complete the quest).
· Exclusive Festival Building Sets and Cloak Patterns.
· A Global Loom goal: all players worldwide contribute Lumen to a community heartstone. When fully charged, a new permanent Cosmology feature is unlocked for everyone (e.g., a new moon for the Hearth sky, or a public park realm where players can meet and chat).

